Dion, Cumberland County District Attorney Jacqueline Sartoris and several Portland city councilors [will hold a news conference](https://www.pressherald.com/2026/01/15/cumberland-county-da-portland-officials-plan-friday-news-conference-on-ice-activity/) about ICE activity on Friday morning, according to officials from the city and DA’s office.

With little concrete information available about if or when an immigration enforcement surge is coming, or what exactly it might entail, organizers throughout the state are staying in close contact and charting possible responses.

